The change in license has come about because of a number of factors:

Years ago, NetBSD changed its OS license to BSD 3 Clause but they didn't remark their old source code files. So Dave asked me to include this in OS notice files: "We have seen organisations and people concerned about the old clause 3 (the advertising clause) in the license, to the extent where NetBSD code could not be used in commercial products; the new license means that these concerns are no longer valid.

